      • DirectoryOnDisk

        public DirectoryOnDisk​(String name)
        A DirectoryOnDisk that does not yet represent an already existing directory on disk, but one that shall be created on disk when calling write(). A parent needs to be defined by calling WritableOnDisk.setParent(app.coronawarn.server.services.distribution.assembly.structure.directory.Directory<app.coronawarn.server.services.distribution.assembly.structure.WritableOnDisk>), before writing can succeed.
        Parameters:
        name - The name that this directory should have on disk.
